/var   
-conatains variable and log data

/var/log 
       -conatins logging file, when u logged in,log out, what command u performed etc. all details

/run
 contains::
 -reaqltime data
 -running services
 -last boot information 
 -media


/run/media/removable media
 -ex info about pendrive,dvd,printer,hard disk etc.


/dev
 -contains device files
  ex::device manager in windows--->identify device detected or not same here

/mnt
 -empty directory
  use:: for ex i created one more partition in linux then to create any mount point in linux. you can use any other file here.


/lib
 -contains library files
 - windows have .dll files running in background supporting windows OS same here


/tmp
-contains temporary files(junk files)
ex:: while installing s/w some junk files created find here


/srv
 -server related information

we have some 
**Post symbolic links(shortcuts)::
/bin --> /usr/bin
/sbin--> /usr/sbin
/lib--> /usr/lib
etc.
for quick access